{As Amended by House Committee of the Whole}
Session of 2025
HOUSE BILL No. 2101
By Committee on Welfare Reform
Requested by Representative Awerkamp
1-27
1 AN ACT concerning public assistance; prohibiting cities and counties
2 from adopting or implementing a guaranteed income program;
3 rendering prior adopted programs null and void; defining guaranteed
4 income program.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. (a) A city or county shall not adopt or enforce an ordinance
8 or resolution, respectively, that establishes or provides for the operation of
9 a guaranteed income program {that uses tax revenue unless the
10 legislature expressly consents to and approves of such program by an
11 act of the legislature}.
12 (b) Any ordinance or resolution prohibited by subsection (a) that was
13 adopted prior to July 1, 2025, shall be null and void.
14 (c) As used in this section, "guaranteed income program" means a
15 program that {is not expressly required by federal law or regulation
16 and} provides individuals with a regular periodic cash payment that may
17 be used for any purpose without requiring such individuals to be
18 employed, seek employment or attend employment-related training to
19 receive such funds.
20 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
21 publication in the statute book.

